==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Centaurea
<hw>Cen`tau*re"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Centaury</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A large genus of
composite plants, related to the thistles and including the cornflower
or bluebottle (<spn>Centaurea Cyanus</spn>) and the star thistle
(<spn>Centaurea Calcitrapa</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centaurium</ent>⟦br⟧
